  "title": "Manager, Regional Medical Affairs",
  "description": "<p>This role focuses on Injectables (Radiesse & Belotero), APAC, and is an integral part of the Medical Affairs support function. The position provides overall management and development of strategies and initiatives supporting the product life cycle management of Radiesse & Belotero. The role is responsible for managing new and current initiatives, driving medical strategies for Merz Dermal Fillers, and ensuring consistency in scientific and clinical messaging to support sales and marketing in Medical Aesthetics<br /><br /><strong>1.    Medical Strategy & Scientific Leadership</strong><br />Provide strategic inputs to develop clinical strength of Radiesse & Belotero with regional KOLs and local scientific associations. Identify and develop innovations, new clinical usage through IITS/clinical research to support product life cycle strategy. Ensure competitive advantages of both Merz products by maintaining updated and proactive clinical support for current, upcoming, and new products within the same therapeutic area. Develop expert meetings/advisory boards to provide guidance and input on products and expansion of clinical usage through innovative treatment practices. Collaborate with internal cross-functional teams and develop novel strategies to support product sustainability and future approaches. Lead diverse internal teams to map product needs and execute new business processes that impact internal strategy and external-facing activities. Ensure critical alignment with both Sales and Marketing in support of the clinical strategies of both Merz products.<br /></p><p><strong>2.   Stakeholder Engagement</strong><br />Consult and interact with internal andexternal stakeholders, including KOLs, Marketing, Sales, Distributors,Regulatory Affairs, Legal & Compliance.<br /><br /><br /><strong>Education</strong>  Advanced degree in Life Sciences,  Pharmacy, Medicine, or related field</p><p><strong>Experiences</strong>  Minimum  8 years’ experience in Medical Affairs positions, primarily in a regional  role (Aesthetics preferred).</p><p><strong>Knowledge, Skill, Attitude</strong>  Sound knowledge of NIS/IITs, medical-pharmaceutical information, sales force  qualification, stakeholder management, E-market, and communication.</p><p>Excellent  communication skills, particularly in stakeholder interactions.  Strong  command in both English and Mandarin  Excellent  written and verbal communication skills.  Willingness  to travel overseas for work, up to 30%.</p>",
